he active report appears misleading, possibly only recognizing API calls from the caller source line. I’m curious if using MethodHandle could hide the stack trace in some cases. I'll definitely need to look into this further!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing NTLM authorization issues**\\n\\nI’m considering whether the NTLM direct call is misdirected due to the class bytes. It appears that NTLMAuthScheme.class$(\\\"io.restassured.authentication.OAuth2Scheme\\\") should work, but maybe the helper class is failing at runtime because of an `IllegalAccessError`. This could be due to package-private access, even if the helper class is defined in the correct package. I wonder if examining existing test results could provide clarity, but the current test results from the workflow may not be updated.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Bxti6uBuzYxpgdck7Zb6BtkR|fc_0feb867ae250d09e016a0082f6661c8195b036141fe3877a0e", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "ls tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/build/test-results/test | grep OAuth || true && ls tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/test-results-native/test | grep OAuth || true"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1056, "output": 1104, "cacheRead": 36352, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38512, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778418401658, "responseId": "resp_0feb867ae250d09e016a0082e2409c81959dcbe057d7c60bc0"}}
